data.title: Michael Dell-Founder, Chairman and Ceo of
data.meta_description: Michael Dell1 - Free download as Powerpoint Presentation (.ppt / .pptx), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or view presentation slides online. Michael Dell founded Dell Computers in 1984 out of his dorm room at the University of Texas at Austin. He started by upgrading computers and applying for state contracts, winning bids due to lower overhead. Dell incorporated the company in 1985 and it grew rapidly, becoming the largest PC maker in 2001. Dell stepped down as CEO in 2004 but returned in 2007, and has received numerous awards and recognition for his entrepreneurship and leadership.
